 <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Add 250 g water and drained rice from simmering basket into mixing bowl and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>. Transfer rice mixture in a bowl, add shrimps, lemon juice, and reserved chopped coriander and mix gently. Without pressing the mixture, fill peppers up to ¾ with shrimp mixture, then replace cut-off top on each pepper and place back into ovenproof dish and set aside."},{"content":"Place remaining 250 g water, 1 tsp vegetable stock paste, 10 g olive oil into mixing bowl and warm it <b>4 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>.  Transfer into ovenproof baking dish with stuffed peppers (liquid should be enough to cover up to 1 cm of the base of the baking dish). Cover with a sheet of aluminium foil and bake for 40-50 minutes (200°C). Remove cover and bake for additional 10 minutes. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve with Yoghurt and cucumber salad."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 25m","6 portions"]}